messages.message:
Some search feedback: @margaret.tomaszczuk
With calibrations ongoing and performance review cycle ending, tried to test Search’s knowledge on the recent cycle, yet getting an outdated source (see screenshot attached and linked here (https://drive.google.com/file/d/1uzwWHYIdH8zoN50JWgZMYUWWDBRijcxK/view)).
A more relevant and up-to-date source would have been: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1cLYW6_xOEzj6IPJMwiKK5TBN9Gphf3rJxirNSeYgG1M/edit?tab=t.0
How can we (and/or future customers) check if a document might (not (yet)) have been indexed?

Also, user error/wishful thinking on my end by making an assumption in the question that I will be eligible for a bonus :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye: Maybe it should have replied: “calibrations are still underway, so bonus payout, *if applicable,* will be …“. :nerd_face:
